# TestRail > Shortcut checklist

Whenever you **create** (or ACC-write) TestRail case(s) for a Shortcut story:

## Required

1. **Immediately** add a Shortcut checklist task on that story (`stories-add-task`).
2. **One checklist item per case** (do not batch multiple case IDs into one task).
3. **Format:**

```text
qa test: <TESTRAIL_BASE_URL>/index.php?/cases/view/<caseId>
```

Resolve `<TESTRAIL_BASE_URL>` from project-context, prefs, or MCP config (never hardcode a company host in this rule).

Example shape:

```text
qa test: https://your-org.testrail.io/index.php?/cases/view/12345
```

## Never

- Suite/section links (`suites/view/...&group_id=...`)
- Run section group links (`runs/view/...&group_id=...`)
- `tests/view/<id>` unless the user explicitly asks for a **run** instance (those IDs are run-specific)

## Flow

`addCase` (get `caseId`) then `stories-add-task` with the format above, in the same turn as the TestRail write.
